      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here are the results for your search:\n\n## \"Adaptive Chameleon or Stubborn Sloth: Revealing the Behavior of Large Language Models in Knowledge Conflicts\"\n\n**Authors:** "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Jian Xie (Fudan University), Kai Zhang (The Ohio State University), Jiangjie Chen (Fudan University), Renze Lou (The Pennsylvania State University), and Yu Su (The Ohio State University)."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n**Venue:** "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Part of International Conference on Learning Representations 2024 (ICLR 2024) Conference."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "It was accepted as an ICLR'24 Spotlight paper."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n**Paper Links:**\n- **arXiv:** https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.13300\n- **OpenReview:** https://openreview.net/forum?id=auKAUJZMO6\n- **GitHub:** https://github.com/OSU-NLP-Group/LLM-Knowledge-Conflict\n\n### Summary\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "By providing external information to large language models (LLMs), tool augmentation (including retrieval augmentation) has emerged as a promising solution for addressing the limitations of LLMs' static parametric memory."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The authors present the first comprehensive and controlled investigation into the behavior of LLMs when encountering knowledge conflicts."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "They propose a systematic framework to elicit high-quality parametric memory from LLMs and construct the corresponding counter-memory, which enables a series of controlled experiments."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n### Key Findings\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The investigation reveals seemingly contradicting behaviors of LLMs. On the one hand, different from prior wisdom, they find that LLMs can be highly receptive to external evidence even when that conflicts with their parametric memory, given that the external evidence is coherent and convincing."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "On the other hand, LLMs also demonstrate a strong confirmation bias when the external evidence contains some information that is consistent with their parametric memory, despite being presented with conflicting evidence at the same time."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "These results pose important implications that are worth careful consideration for the further development and deployment of tool- and retrieval-augmented LLMs."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In short, the paper explores whether LLMs are \"Adaptive Chameleons,\" open to external evidence, or \"Stubborn Sloths,\" holding onto parametric memory."
      }
    ],
